The augment function
The augment function takes a data frame and ‚Äúaugments‚Äù it by adding three new columns on the left that describe the model predictions for each row:


.pred_class: model prediction (\(\hat{y}\)) based on a 50% threshold;

.pred_0: model estimate of \(P(y=0)\);

.pred_1: model estimate of \(P(y=1) = 1 - P(y = 0)\).

