The bottom line, at the top

We do not know what the ‚Äútrue‚Äù line is;
Our estimates are a best guess based on noisy, incomplete, imperfect data;
The more data we have, the more ‚Äúcertain‚Äù and ‚Äúreliable‚Äù the estimates are;
What do we mean by ‚Äúuncertainty‚Äù here?

Sampling uncertainty

Fact: different data set -&gt; different estimates;

How much would our estimate vary across alternative datasets?

If the answer is ‚Äúa lot,‚Äù uncertainty is high, and our estimates are not super reliable;
If the answer is ‚Äúa little,‚Äù uncertainty is low, and maybe we can take our estimates to the bank;

